		}
		{
			dependencies: ["453608F7110E1D8E"]
			description: ["GregTech tools till farmland at standard speed for their material tier. An iron hoe is sufficient for a moderate-scale farm — tilling range, not growth speed, is the only thing that scales with material. What matters most is crop placement: a 9x9 centered on a single water source maximizes yield density per water block. Invest in a Botany Pot setup for crops that do not scale with field area, and reserve field plots for high-volume staples like wheat, tomato, and rice."]
			id: "0487B5BA7036BFC5"
